ENTRY       EC 2.4.1.116                Enzyme
NAME        cyanidin 3-O-rutinoside 5-O-glucosyltransferase;
            uridine diphosphoglucose-cyanidin 3-rhamnosylglucoside 5-O-glucosyltransferase;
            cyanidin-3-rhamnosylglucoside 5-O-glucosyltransferase;
            UDP-glucose:cyanidin-3-O-D-rhamnosyl-1,6-D-glucoside 5-O-D-glucosyltransferase
CLASS       Transferases;
            Glycosyltransferases;
            Hexosyltransferases
SYSNAME     UDP-alpha-D-glucose:cyanidin-3-O-alpha-L-rhamnosyl-(1->6)-beta-D-glucoside 5-O-beta-D-glucosyltransferase
REACTION    UDP-alpha-D-glucose + cyanidin-3-O-rutinoside = UDP + cyanidin 3-O-rutinoside 5-O-beta-D-glucoside [RN:R06819]
ALL_REAC    R06819;
            (other) R06803
SUBSTRATE   UDP-alpha-D-glucose [CPD:C00029];
            cyanidin-3-O-rutinoside
PRODUCT     UDP [CPD:C00015];
            cyanidin 3-O-rutinoside 5-O-beta-D-glucoside [CPD:C12646]
COMMENT     Isolated from the plants Silene dioica (red campion) [1], Iris ensata (Japanese iris) [2] and Iris hollandica (Dutch iris) [3]. Also acts on the 3-O-rutinosides of pelargonidin, delphinidin and malvidin, but not the corresponding glucosides or 6-acylglucosides. The enzyme does not catalyse the glucosylation of the 5-hydroxy group of cyanidin 3-glucoside.
HISTORY     EC 2.4.1.116 created 1984 (EC 2.4.1.235 created 2004, incorporated 2006), modified 2006, modified 2013
